&ldquo;The question I am asked most often when speaking about hunger, war, trafficking, disease, or poverty is, What can I do? I’ve never been asked, Who must I become? Doing justice well is important, but who we become is equally — if not more — important.&rdquo;
Stephan Bauman
In a world filled with brokenness, it&rsquo;s simply not enough to want to help. The world is filled with people who have a desire to assist their neighbor in loving and meaningful ways, and yet so many of these goodhearted people lack the resources, skills, education, and time to serve their neighbor in meaningful, effective ways.
